    <string name="privacy_storage_title">Stored on this device</string>
    <string name="privacy_storage_body">KGS Calendar stores events, tasks, reminders, settings, source names, server URLs, usernames, and cached calendar data on this device. CalDAV passwords and app passwords are stored in Android encrypted preferences and are excluded from Android app backup.</string>
    <string name="privacy_sync_title">Sync and accounts</string>
    <string name="privacy_sync_body">If you add a CalDAV/Nextcloud account, an ICS URL, or Android device calendars, the app uses the configured server, URL, or Android Calendar Provider so syncing can work. KGS Calendar has no ads, analytics SDKs, tracking SDKs, or developer-operated backend.</string>
    <string name="privacy_location_title">Location search and maps</string>
    <string name="privacy_location_body">Location search is optional. When you press Search, the query is sent to OpenStreetMap Nominatim. If you choose nearby results, approximate device location is used to bias that search. Map previews are loaded from OpenStreetMap only after you choose to show a preview, unless automatic previews are enabled below.</string>
    <string name="privacy_delete_title">Deleting local data</string>
    <string name="privacy_delete_body">Removing a calendar source deletes its local credentials and cached data but leaves server calendars unchanged. The separate “Delete server calendar” action permanently deletes that calendar from its CalDAV server. Uninstalling the app deletes local app data from this device.</string>
